Join Our Exceptional Team
Where excellence is a team effort
Located in the heart of Naples, Florida, Wyndemere Country Club is a premier private club known for its Arthur Hills-designed 27-hole golf course, active lifestyle programming, and world-class amenities—including tennis, pickleball, croquet, bocce, a resort-style pool, fitness center, spa services, and multiple dining venues. Recognized as both a Platinum Club of America and a Distinguished Club of the World, Wyndemere sets the standard for excellence in the private club industry.
Whether in Food & Beverage, Culinary, Locker Room, Golf, Racquet Sports, Fitness, or Maintenance, our employees take pride in a culture built on Teamwork and a shared commitment to providing outstanding service to our Members and their guests.

Why work at wyndemere?
At Wyndemere, our greatest asset is our people.
As one of only 150 Platinum Clubs of America, we’re known for our warm, welcoming atmosphere where
“Ladies and Gentlemen serve Ladies and Gentlemen.”
When you join our Team, you become part of a community that values professionalism, authentic hospitality, and genuine camaraderie.
Here, you are encouraged to greet every Member and guest with a smile, work collaboratively with your colleagues, and take pride in consistently exceeding expectations.

TEAM Culture & Growth Opportunities
At Wyndemere, Teamwork is the foundation of everything we do. From day one, you'll be part of a
supportive environment where collaboration, communication, and mutual respect thrive
. Whether you're interacting with Members or working behind the scenes, you’ll have clear expectations and opportunities for growth through mentorship, cross-training, and career advancement.
We also take pride in recognizing our Team. Monthly awards, milestone celebrations, and long-term acknowledgments highlight the value we place on dedication. Here, you're not just building a career—
you’re joining a Team that grows and celebrates together.
End Mini-Page 22305

Frequently asked questions
1. Can I work year-round at Wyndemere?
Yes—many of our core roles (club operations, grounds, and certain support positions) are staffed year-round to ensure consistent service and facility upkeep. Some seasonal roles are typically tied to peak season, but we strive to transition high-performing seasonal Team members into other year-round openings whenever possible.
2. How does Wyndemere foster a positive company culture and support the well-being of its employees?
We prioritize teamwork, communication, and recognition. From monthly celebrations and service awards to free meals and access to wellness facilities, we invest in our Team. Ongoing feedback, check-ins, and growth opportunities help every employee feel valued and supported.
3. Do you hire international workers?
Yes. We participate in the H-2B seasonal program and have a limited number of year-round positions open to visa-eligible candidates. All international hires must meet U.S. work authorization requirements.

The Wyndemere Story
Our Community's Legacy
Located in the Heart of Naples, Florida
Wyndemere Country Club's founding father, Gerald Livingston, envisioned a community unlike any other in Southwest Florida. He purchased a 450-acre tract of land with the hopes it would one day become a hub of social activity providing recreation, enjoyment and friendship for its Members. Wyndemere Country Club opened its gates in 1981. Mr. Livingston's vision and passion continue on here today. The bond between Members and sense of community that's felt by so many is a testament to those ideals.
Cheri schwartz,CMP - Membership Director
For tours or membership inquiries, please contact Cheri Schwartz, Membership Director, at 239-643-6336 (direct) or email
[email protected]
.

Universal Recognition
Our Members hail from all walks of life across the planet. Members have come far and wide, from as far west as California, from northern Nordic countries such as Sweden, and even Panama! This global Membership has helped to instill a strong sense of community values within the Club and is a key contributing factor to the phrase, "It's the people that make Wyndemere special!"
Contact Us

The philosophy of Wyndemere Country Club is governed by these core principles that direct the decisions we make; define our character; and preserve our culture.

Begin Mini-Page 22372
Our Mission
At Wyndemere we are committed to providing current and future Members, their families, and guests with an exceptional experience.
Provide Outstanding Amenities
Whether it's golf, racquet sports, bocce, croquet, wellness facilities, or dining, Wyndemere provides world-class amenities for our Members, their families, and guests to enjoy.
Promote Excellent Service
We promise exceptional service levels in all venues through a highly engaged management team and professional staff.
Value our Sense of Community
We are Member-owned; all community residents are Members of our Club. We value our size that allows us to offer a welcoming and inclusive Membership devoted to the enrichment of life through a sense of community, friendship, and recreation.
End Mini-Page 22372
end panelSection
Begin Mini-Page 22373
End Mini-Page 22373
Begin Mini-Page 22374
Our Vision
At Wyndemere we continuously strive to preserve and strengthen ourselves as the premier private golf & country club community in Naples, FL by offering the finest facilities, activities, services, and staff in a fiscally sound manner.
Continuous Improvement
Wyndemere's dedication to continuous improvement ensures that our community is able to provide exceptional amenities on an ongoing basis
Strategic Governance and Management
We are governed by a Board of Directors who sets strategy, objectives, and goals and provides long term vision while extending open interaction with our Membership
Prudent Fiscal Management
We manage our finances with prudence and diligence to preserve the long-term financial stability and security of our Club.
End Mini-Page 22374

Whether you're looking for your next game, glass of wine or just a place to unwind, Wyndemere is a club you'll want to keep coming back to.
